HEADWORD: Polychæta
<hw>Pol`y*ch⟦ae⟧"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
from Gr. <grk>poly`s</grk> many + <?/ hair.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of the two principal groups of Ch⟦ae⟧topoda. It includes those
